  <title>Manage priorities.</title>


  <sect2>
    <title>roles priority setting</title>

    <para>All roles have configurable priority order under <emphasis role="bold">«Project administration/Your memberships/Your roles»</emphasis>, by pressing the arrows in the column priority <emphasis role="bold">«ORDER»</emphasis> :</para>
      <figure>
       <title>Priority order</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center"
                     fileref="041-04-RolePriorities.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    </sect2>
    
     <sect2>
     <title>Setting the priority roles for users and groups</title>
     <para>If administrator has not selected the <emphasis role="bold">«PRIORITARY»</emphasis> chekbox when associating a group or user in the project, the priority of user roles or groups remains unchanged.</para>
      
      
      <sect3>
    <title>Use Case</title>
    <para>Here the "Validator" role of user has higher priority than the "Reporter" role. This is visible (in bold) in the column <emphasis role="bold">«ROLES»</emphasis> :</para>
     <figure>
     <title>Change Priority</title>
     <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center"
                     fileref="041-04-PrioritieUseCase.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
     <para>If the administrator assigns priority to the "Reporter" role, then  "Validator" will have a higher priority than the "Validator" role :</para>
      <figure>
      <title>Change Priority</title>
     <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata align="center"
                     fileref="041-04-PrioritieUseCaseChange.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    </sect3> 
     </sect2>  
